#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/taxonomy-interpretation.adoc:366
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "Occurrence download predicates"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/nav.adoc:16
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "API Downloads"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The GBIF Occurrence Download API provides a service to download occurrence "
"records and retrieve information about those downloads."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Occurrence downloads are created asynchronously — the user requests a "
"download and, once the download is prepared, is sent an email with a link to "
"the resulting file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:8
msgid ""
"It is necessary to register as a user on https://www.gbif.org/[GBIF.org] to "
"create a download request, and to authenticate using the username (not the "
"email) and password."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:10
msgid ""
"Complete technical details are provided in the xref:v1@openapi::occurrence."
"adoc#/tag/Occurrence-downloads[API reference documentation]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Requesting an occurrence download"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:14
msgid ""
"A download request includes your username, email address, the download "
"format, and a filter for the required data in the form of a <<predicates,"
"predicate>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:16
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-sql-downloads.adoc:20
msgid "A basic example using the _curl_ command to make the request:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Put this in a file called `query.json`, replacing `userName` with your "
"username and `userEmail@example.org` with your email address:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:42
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [ \"userEmail@example.org\" ],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"format\": \"SIMPLE_CSV\",\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"and\",\n"
"    \"predicates\": [\n"
"      {\n"
"        \"type\": \"equals\",\n"
"        \"key\": \"BASIS_OF_RECORD\",\n"
"        \"value\": \"PRESERVED_SPECIMEN\"\n"
"      },\n"
"      {\n"
"        \"type\": \"in\",\n"
"        \"key\": \"COUNTRY\",\n"
"        \"values\": [ \"VC\", \"GD\" ]\n"
"      }\n"
"    ]\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:45
msgid ""
"`format` can be changed to one of `SIMPLE_CSV`, `DWCA` or `SPECIES_LIST`, "
"see https://www.gbif.org/faq?question=download-formats[information about "
"download formats]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:47
msgid "Then use this Curl command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "curl --include --user userName:PASSWORD --header \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data @query.json https://api.gbif.org/v1/occurrence/download/request\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:54
msgid ""
"A download key is returned. Querying that download key shows the download "
"information, including the download link and DOI once the download is "
"ready.  Run this repeatedly, until you see `SUCCEEDED`, replacing the key "
"with the key for your download:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "curl -Ss https://api.gbif.org/v1/occurrence/download/0001005-130906152512535\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:61
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-sql-downloads.adoc:62
msgid "You can then download the resulting file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "curl --location --remote-name https://api.gbif.org/occurrence/download/request/0001005-130906152512535.zip\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:70
msgid ""
"Downloads using predicates can also be made through the website at https://"
"www.gbif.org/occurrence/download/request[create new download]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "Occurrence search parameters"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:76
msgid ""
"Most of the predicates below use a `key` which specifies the field to search "
"on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:78
msgid ""
"The keys are listed and described on the xref:v1@openapi::occurrence.adoc#/"
"Searching%20occurrences/searchOccurrence[/occurrence/search API call], and "
"in the https://gbif.github.io/gbif-api/apidocs/org/gbif/api/model/occurrence/"
"search/OccurrenceSearchParameter.html[Java documentation].  Note they must "
"be provided in `UPPER_CASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES` for the download APIs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:83
msgid ""
"These are the supported predicates that can be combined to build download "
"requests."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "`equals`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:87
msgid ""
"Equality comparison.  Tests for exact equality of the term and the value, or "
"case-sensitive equality if `matchCase` is set to `true`."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"equals\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"BASIS_OF_RECORD\",\n"
"    \"value\": \"LITERATURE\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:103
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:119
msgid "or"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:116
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"equals\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"HAS_COORDINATE\",\n"
"    \"value\": \"true\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:133
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"equals\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"CATALOG_NUMBER\",\n"
"    \"value\": \"Ax1\",\n"
"    \"matchCase\":\"true\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "`and`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:138
msgid "Logical conjuction, \"and\".  The sub-predicates must all be true."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:153
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"and\",\n"
"    \"predicates\": [\n"
"      { \"type\": \"equals\", \"key\": \"HAS_GEOSPATIAL_ISSUE\", \"value\": \"false\"},\n"
"      { \"type\": \"equals\", \"key\": \"TAXON_KEY\", \"value\": \"59R5F\", \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\" }\n"
"    ]\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:155
#, no-wrap
msgid "`or`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:158
msgid ""
"Logical disjunction, \"or\". At least one of the sub-predicates must be true."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:160
msgid ""
"When requesting many values of the same field (for example, multiple taxa or "
"countries) the `in` predicate (just below) is more appropriate."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"or\",\n"
"    \"predicates\": [\n"
"      { \"type\": \"equals\", \"key\": \"HAS_GEOSPATIAL_ISSUE\", \"value\": \"false\"},\n"
"      { \"type\": \"equals\", \"key\": \"TAXON_KEY\", \"value\": \"59R5F\", \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\" }\n"
"    ]\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:177
#, no-wrap
msgid "`in`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:180
msgid ""
"Specify multiple values to be compared.  `\"matchCase\": true` can be added "
"if required."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:193
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"in\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"CATALOG_NUMBER\",\n"
"    \"values\": [\"cat1\", \"cat2\", \"cat3\"]\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:195
#, no-wrap
msgid "`lessThan`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:198
msgid ""
"Less than.  Returns occurrences with term values strictly less than the "
"provided value."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:211
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"lessThan\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"YEAR\",\n"
"    \"value\": \"1900\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "`lessThanOrEquals`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:216
msgid ""
"Less than or equals.  Returns occurrences with term values less than or "
"equal to the provided value."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:229
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"lessThanOrEquals\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"ELEVATION\",\n"
"    \"value\": \"1000\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:231
#, no-wrap
msgid "`greaterThan`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:234
msgid ""
"Greater than.  Returns occurrences with term values strictly greater than "
"the provided value."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:247
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"greaterThan\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"YEAR\",\n"
"    \"value\": \"1900\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:249
#, no-wrap
msgid "`greaterThanOrEquals`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:252
msgid ""
"Greater than or equals. Returns occurrences with term values greater than or "
"equal to the provided value"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:265
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"greaterThanOrEquals\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"ELEVATION\",\n"
"    \"value\": \"1000\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:267
#, no-wrap
msgid "`within`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:270
msgid ""
"Geospatial predicate that checks if the coordinates are inside a polygon."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:272
msgid ""
"The polygon should be specified in https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Well-"
"known_text_representation_of_geometry[Well-known text (WKT)] format.  If you "
"have problems, first check your polygon with https://arthur-e.github.io/"
"Wicket/[Wicket] — ensure the points are ordered anti-clockwise.  (A polygon "
"with clockwise points represents the opposite: the whole world _except_ the "
"polygon.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:288
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"within\",\n"
"    \"geometry\": \"POLYGON((-130.78125 51.179342,\n"
"                          -130.78125 22.593726,\n"
"                          -62.578125 22.593726,\n"
"                          -62.578125 51.179342,\n"
"                          -130.78125 51.179342))\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "`geoDistance`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:293
msgid ""
"Geospatial distance.  This predicate checks if coordinates are within a "
"specified distance of a geographical coordinate.  The distance is specified "
"with a unit, e.g. `5km` or `1250m`."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:307
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"geoDistance\",\n"
"    \"latitude\": \"90\",\n"
"    \"longitude\": \"100\",\n"
"    \"distance\": \"5km\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "`not`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:312
msgid "Logical negation.  Gives the opposite of the sub-predicate."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:328
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"not\",\n"
"    \"predicate\": {\n"
"      \"type\": \"equals\",\n"
"      \"key\": \"DATASET_KEY\",\n"
"      \"value\": \"4fa7b334-ce0d-4e88-aaae-2e0c138d049e\"\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:330
#, no-wrap
msgid "`like`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:333
msgid ""
"Search for a pattern. `?` matches exactly one character, `*` matches zero or "
"more characters.  `\"matchCase\": true` can be added if required."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:346
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"like\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"CATALOG_NUMBER\",\n"
"    \"value\": \"PAPS5-560*\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:348
#, no-wrap
msgid "`isNull`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:351
msgid "Has an empty (null) value."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:363
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"isNull\",\n"
"    \"parameter\": \"CONTINENT\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:365
#, no-wrap
msgid "`isNotNull`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:368
msgid "Has a non-empty value"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:380
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"isNotNull\",\n"
"    \"parameter\":\"ISSUE\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:383
#, no-wrap
msgid "Predicate support for multiple taxonomies"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:386
msgid ""
"the `equals`, `in` support multiple taxonomies by adding a `checklistKey` "
"property to the predicate."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:400
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"equals\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"TAXON_KEY\",\n"
"    \"value\": \"5WZLF\",\n"
"    \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:415
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userName@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"in\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"TAXON_KEY\",\n"
"    \"value\": [\"BSJCX\", \"3BQFW\"],\n"
"    \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:420
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloads with a specific taxonomy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:423
msgid ""
"Users can specify the taxonomy to be included in occurrence downloads by "
"adding the `checklistKey` parameter to the download request. *If no "
"`checklistKey` is supplied the obsolete GBIF Backbone Taxonomy will be used."
"* The `checklistKey` should be specified for the whole request (for the "
"taxonomy used for output) as well as in taxonomic filters."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:438
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"notificationAddresses\": [\"userEmail@example.org\"],\n"
"  \"sendNotification\": true,\n"
"  \"format\": \"SIMPLE_CSV\",\n"
"  \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\" <1>\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    \"type\": \"equals\",\n"
"    \"key\": \"TAXON_KEY\",\n"
"    \"checklistKey\": \"7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-b351-99906754a03b\", <2>\n"
"    \"value\": \"5WZLF\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:440
msgid ""
"Use the https://www.gbif.org/dataset/7ddf754f-d193-4cc9-"
"b351-99906754a03b[Catalogue of Life] for the output, i.e. `species`, "
"`scientificName`, `taxonKey` etc columns"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:441
msgid ""
"Use the Catalogue of Life for filtering to taxon https://www.gbif.org/"
"taxon/5WZLF[5WZLF (_Carcharodon carcharias_)]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:443
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verbatim extension data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:446
msgid ""
"A download in Darwin Core Archive (`DWCA`) format includes three tables by "
"default, as described in detail on xref::download-formats.adoc[Occurrence "
"download formats]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:448
msgid ""
"Additional Darwin Core extension data can also be included in the archive.  "
"These data tables are not processed by GBIF; they are as-published."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:450
msgid ""
"The extension tables available for download are provided using https://api."
"gbif.org/v1/occurrence/download/describe/dwca[this API call], under "
"`verbatimExtensions`.  They can be requested by adding a "
"`verbatimExtensions` property to the download request:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:463
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"format\": \"DWCA\",\n"
"  \"predicate\": {\n"
"    …\n"
"  },\n"
"  \"verbatimExtensions\": [\n"
"    \"http://rs.gbif.org/terms/1.0/DNADerivedData\",\n"
"    \"http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/MeasurementOrFact\"\n"
"  ]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/api-downloads.adoc:465
msgid ""
"For descriptions of the extensions and their terms, see https://rs.gbif.org/"
"extensions.html[GBIF Registered Extensions]."
msgstr ""
